Thank you Team 17 for porting this over to mobile devices. The game is great, but there's room for improvement: Sometimes a guard will stand still and float over the walls. This bug happens every so often; When all the prisoners and the guards come to the same room, that impacts the game's performance; In the Craft Menu, you have to use the d-pads or left stick to highlight the item you can craft AND the level required. That makes finding the item you're looking for more time-consuming. Isn't it possible to use the right stick to browse the LEVELS required and the left stick to check the item from that level? Also, when playing the game for the first time, a popup will show up asking for which kind of touch input the user would like to use, even though the game has already detected a physical controller. Either A) make the popup disappear after the game has detected a physical controller or B) include the option to use a physical controller in the popup; The game currently supports only English for the dialogs and in-game instructions (I can handle the translation to PT if you'd like, please get in touch); Please add more maps via game updates in the future. Up Next: Overcooked ;-)
